  "why": "The paper demonstrates cross-model transferability by reusing prompts found on one model against others (see Section IV-B and Table VI). However, the PAIR algorithm’s design is focused on iterative attacker–target refinement (attack generation, target response, scoring, iterative refinement) and on crafting interpretable prompt templates; it does not include explicit mechanisms or optimization objectives aimed at discovering transferable failures (for example, guiding mutations using surrogate-model feedback or explicitly optimizing for transfer). Therefore it shows demonstrated transferability without having been explicitly designed for transfer.",
